    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="163"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName> Mission files, lot 57 M 38,
                        “<gloss target="#t_CSC1">CSC</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss>
                    Relations”: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 163<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Special Representative in Europe (<persName
                            corresp="#p_DRAPERWHJ1" type="from">Draper</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Mutual Security Agency</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d163fn1">Repeated to Luxembourg.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-21">March 21,
                            1953</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Repto1">Repto</gloss> 2812. Washington pass State. Subj.:
                    Relations between <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> and European Coal and
                    Steel Community.</p>
                <pb facs="0346" n="298" xml:id="pg_298"/>
                <p>The <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> Council at official level meeting March
                        20<note n="2" xml:id="d163fn2">The minutes of this 208th meeting of the
                            <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> Council, which took place in Paris
                        on Mar. 20, are in <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> files, lot 56 D
                        217, “C/M(53)1 through 10”.</note> adopted resolution providing for closer
                    working relationship with High Authority.<note n="3" xml:id="d163fn3">The text
                        of this resolution, which was circulated as Council document C(53)
                        86(Final), is in <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> files, lot 56 D 217,
                        “C(53)86”.</note> Austria and Portugal accepted ad referendum. Main point of
                    resolution invites <gloss target="#t_HA1">HA</gloss> to send observer to <gloss
                        target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> meetings of Council and Exec Comite, when
                    discussions in <gloss target="#t_HA1">HA</gloss> judgment have bearing on <gloss
                        target="#t_CSC1">CSC</gloss> activities. Observer also invited to meetings
                    Coal, Iron and Steel, Inland Transport, Manpower, and Joint Trade-Payments
                    Comites, and any bodies engaged in study questions relating investment.
                    Attendance at meetings other technical comites to be decided by Exec Comite
                    after discussion with Chmn comite concerned. Documents relating to work those
                    groups whose meetings observer will attend are to be made available to <gloss
                        target="#t_HA1">HA</gloss>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Non-members of <gloss target="#t_CSC1">CSC</gloss>, led by
                            <persName>Bartels</persName> of Den, again stressed “one-way street”
                        aspect of relationships with <gloss target="#t_HA1">HA</gloss> and found
                        resolution unsatisfactory in that no exchange of views provided for.
                            <persName corresp="#p_CATTANIA1">Cattani</persName>, Italy as Chmn of
                        working party concerned with preparing resolution stated that present draft
                        was best that could be arranged for present.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>On urging from <persName>Bartels</persName> that Min Council on Monday not
                        be faced with necessity debating draft resolution, because of difficult
                        political position in which non-members <gloss target="#t_CSC1">CSC</gloss>
                        would be placed, it was agreed that Ministers would merely be informed of
                        action which had been taken at official level.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DRAPERWHJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Draper</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
